((date 2026-07-05) (slug continuation-add-v2-surface)
 (hypothesis
  "Continuation-add v2 (mechanism #1855, plan #1852): the book's ACTUAL continuation buy (Ch. 3 The Trader's Way) as the scale-in add trigger — full-size initial entries (no explore-side tax) + full-size adds on a consolidation-near-rising-MA breakout with volume confirmation. The untested 'press-the-winner' half left open by the v1 REJECT: does adding into book-defined revealed strength beat the flat full-unit baseline on WF-CV?")
 (base_scenario "BROAD-ONLY surface (top-3000 PIT-2000, the decisive cell; no sp500 per user directive 2026-07-04), 2000-2026, 13x2y non-overlapping folds, production caps (0.30/0.70/0.30) + catstop 0.10, Cell-E long-only + stage3/laggard, snapshot warehouse fork-per-fold.")
 (window_id surface-broadonly-top3000-wfcv-2000-2026-13fold-2y)
 (baseline_label baseline)
 (variants
  (((label baseline) (config_hash "")
    (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.5970) (mean_calmar 0.6830) (mean_return_pct 19.920) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 15.360)))))
   ((label cont_add) (config_hash "contadd-1.0-consbreak-ext0.25")
    (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.5670) (mean_calmar 0.6140) (mean_return_pct 19.230) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 15.660)))))
   ((label cont_add_tight) (config_hash "contadd-1.0-consbreak-ext0.25-band0.06")
    (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.5660) (mean_calmar 0.6250) (mean_return_pct 19.120) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 15.200)))))
   ((label cont_add_vol) (config_hash "contadd-1.0-consbreak-ext0.25-vol1.5")
    (aggregate (((mean_sharpe 0.5950) (mean_calmar 0.6700) (mean_return_pct 20.230) (mean_max_drawdown_pct 15.650)))))))
 (verdict Reject)
 (notes
  "REJECT for promotion; mechanism KEEPS default-off axis status; SCALE-IN PROGRAM CLOSED (both halves now tested: v1 half-sizing = fat-tail tax; v2 full-size + book-faithful continuation adds = flat redistribution). Gate FAIL all variants (Sharpe wins 4/13, 3/13, 4/13 < 7; cont_add/tight worst-fold f007 gap 0.497 > 0.30; cont_add_vol passes worst-delta at 0.172 but lands DEAD ON baseline 0.595 vs 0.597). Pre-run sanity: adds emit AND fill (COHU sibling verified; trades.csv trustworthy post-#1847). THE TRANSFERABLE WHYs: (1) THE FAITHFUL TRIGGER IS RARE BY DESIGN = LOW POWER — 5-6 of 13 folds bit-identical to baseline (stacked gates: 4wk tight band near MA + volume + not-late + ext 0.25 + max_adds 1 admit only a handful of adds per 2y fold); the aggregate is decided by a few fold-level coin flips. (2) REGIME-MIXED WHEN IT FIRES: fold-010 (2020-21 monsters) the press works exactly as the book says (+10.7pp, Sharpe 1.30->1.41, DD flat); fold-007 (2014-15) the same press hits mean-reversion (-15.7pp, Sharpe 1.16->0.66). (3) VOLUME CONFIRMATION IS THE LOAD-BEARING DIAL — the book's 'impressive volume' emphasis is empirically right: vol 1.5x blocks exactly the fold-007 damage (29.77 vs baseline 30.15) while keeping the fold-010 win, but the harm-filtered variant is baseline-flat: removing the bad adds removes the edge too. (4) ROOT CAUSE, 9th edge_is_the_fat_tail confirmation from a NEW angle: under the always-binding cash constraint (~10 Insufficient_cash skips/Friday) a full-size add is FINANCED BY DISPLACED NEW ENTRIES — even the book's own trader-mode press-the-winner is reallocation INTO held winners OUT OF breadth, and breadth IS the edge; the redistribution nets zero at best. FORWARD GUIDANCE: stop proposing intra-envelope capital-reallocation variants — the class is exhausted (v1, v2, harvest-rotate, laggard-cap, macro-trim all dead). If continuation-adds are EVER revisited, pair them with an ENVELOPE change (min_cash/max_exposure sweep — never done as a pair) so the add is not financed by starved breadth. Ops: 9h06m wall, 52 fold-runs, zero failures; Docker.raw preflight fixed non-destructively (55->21GB, container /tmp scratch). Artifacts: dev/experiments/continuation-add-v2-2026-07-05/ (spec, out_top3000, sanity). Writeup: dev/notes/continuation-add-v2-wfcv-2026-07-05.md."))
